<!-- Staff Retention -->
<div class="section">
  <h1 class="slide-title">5. Staff Retention ‚Üí Brand Connection</h1>
  <p class="slide-subtitle">The paradox between employee reviews and testimonial praise</p>
  
  <h2 class="section-title">The Retention Paradox</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Source</th>
        <th>Rating/Sentiment</th>
        <th>Key Feedback</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Glassdoor</td>
        <td>2.6/5</td>
        <td>Employee satisfaction concerns</td>
      </tr>
      <tr class="highlight-row">
        <td>Testimonials</td>
        <td>9.6/10 staff score</td>
        <td>"Staff who love their jobs," 5-20 year tenure, 78% praise rate</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  
  <div class="card card-warning">
    <h4>‚ö†Ô∏è The Contradiction</h4>
    <p><strong>Testimonials:</strong> "The staff is wonderful... they treat residents with respect and truly care."</p>
    <p><strong>Employee Reviews:</strong> Low satisfaction, turnover concerns</p>
    <p><strong>Hypothesis:</strong> Either (a) reviews skew toward disgruntled ex-employees, or (b) front-line staff love the work but struggle with management/compensation.</p>
  </div>
  
  <h2 class="section-title">Industry Staff Turnover Crisis (2024-2025)</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Role</th>
        <th>2024 Turnover</th>
        <th>2025 Turnover</th>
        <th>Replacement Cost</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>CNAs</td>
        <td>44.16%</td>
        <td>42.34%</td>
        <td>$5,000-$10,000</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Resident Assistants</td>
        <td>44.46%</td>
        <td>43.25%</td>
        <td>$5,000-$10,000</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Registered Nurses</td>
        <td>High</td>
        <td>Declining</td>
        <td>$46,100 (87 days)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Top Executives</td>
        <td>31.97%</td>
        <td>22.12%</td>
        <td>$100,000+</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  
  <p style="margin-top: 16px; color: hsl(215, 15%, 55%);">Overall assisted living: 34.53% average turnover (2025)</p>
  
  <div class="card card-highlight">
    <h4>üìä Impact on Care Quality & Brand</h4>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>10% turnover increase = 4.0% more health citations</strong></li>
      <li>High turnover facilities (135% median) = 1-star CMS ratings</li>
      <li>Low turnover facilities (76.7% median) = 5-star CMS ratings</li>
      <li>More rehospitalizations, physical restraints, infections with high turnover</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  
  <h2 class="section-title">Financial Impact</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Staffing = 55%+ of total operating expenses</strong></li>
    <li>Average fall-related claim: $275,495 (assisted living)</li>
    <li>Turnover costs: Recruiting, training, productivity loss, cultural deterioration</li>
  </ul>
  
  <div class="card card-success">
    <h4>‚úÖ American House Opportunity: Turn Staff into Brand Ambassadors</h4>
    <p><strong>Strengths to Leverage:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Testimonials praise staff longevity (5-20 years)</li>
      <li>"Family atmosphere" mentioned 3x more than competitors</li>
      <li>9.6/10 staff score in testimonial analysis</li>
    </ul>
    <p style="margin-top: 16px;"><strong>Strategic Initiatives:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Close the Employee Experience Gap</strong> ‚Äî Audit why Glassdoor is 2.6/5 if testimonials praise staff</li>
      <li><strong>Amplify Staff Stories</strong> ‚Äî Feature long-tenured staff in marketing, "Meet the Team" videos</li>
      <li><strong>Culture-First Positioning</strong> ‚Äî "Staff Who Love What They Do" vs. corporate competitors</li>
      <li><strong>Retention ROI Tracking</strong> ‚Äî Every 10% reduction = 4% fewer citations = higher star ratings = revenue growth</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

